<text>Inserting a feedback area

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

Feedback boxes embedded in HTML pages are common. But setting up a feedback box in a Web page is usually hard for non-programmers --- it requires a server and some programming.

In MW, this task is made very easy --- we provide you a server and have done the programming for you. All you need to do is to place the caret to the location you would want the feedback area to be, select the &quot;Insert&gt;Miscellaneous Components&gt;Feedback Area&quot; menu (keyboard shortcut ALT+SHIFT+E), and click the OK button in the dialog window that pops up. The pop-up dialog window, which looks like the following image:

  
&#12304;This is a screenshot.&#12305;
 
allows you to set the size, transparency of the text area, and border of the feedback area.

You can insert a feedback area to any MW page to collect user feedback on the model and activity you designed. Feedback will be seen by anyone playing the activity. If you submit a new comment, you can click the &quot;Update&quot; button below the text area to see your comment, or simply reload the whole page using the &quot;Reload&quot; button.

Changing and removing a feedback area

See &quot;Editing an embedded component&quot; for how to change, move, remove and copy a feedback area.

A feedback area is placed below for you to experiment with this functionality.

 
